 richmond british columbia and the creation of three main operating segments chc global operations based in richmond bc chc european operations based in aberdeen scotland and helione chcs leasing and repair and overhaul support group now based in delta bc in february  all of chcs shares were purchased by first reserve a us private equity company for cad billion  billion at the time the word corporation was dropped from the companys name which is now simply chc helicopter on january   chc announced an initial public offering of  shares first reserve now holds  of chcs shares on th jan  chc offered  shares at us on  may  chc helicopters filed for chapter  bankruptcy chc shares dropped from us th nov  to us cents  june  a texas court allowed chc in july  to shed  helicopters from its financial obligations most of the super pumas chc reorganized in march  divisionsedit chc manages its global operations through the following divisions eea helicopter operations bv eea a dutch company majority owned by eho holdings sarl and minority owned by chc helicopter sarl provides helicopter services in the north sea eea operates under the chc brand name and uses chc logo under licence it provides services from  bases in the uk ireland denmark norway and the netherlands brazilian helicopter services bhs brazil chc helicopters global operationscorporate office richmond british columbia chc helicopters australia chc helicopters africa chc composites gander newfoundland chc ems and sar servicesedit irelandedit chc s operated for the irish coast guard chc helicopter serves as the sole provider of search and rescue helicopter services to the irish coast guard where it had operated a fleet of six sikorsky sn helicopters based in dublin shannon waterford and sligo this fleet has now been replaced by  sikorsky s helibus the sn exited service in december  with a flight from dublin airport to weston aerodrome west dublin the flight was operated by eisar the oldest sn in commercial operation at the time united kingdomedit chc currently provides sar helicopters to two of the four maritime and coastguard agency bases in the uk portland leeonsolent and until recently also operated from sumburgh and stornoway chc as part of the soteria sar consortium was selected as the preferred bidder for a year contract to provide a civilian search and rescue service throughout the united kingdom however days before the contract was due to be signed in february  the british government halted the process after chc disclosed that it had unauthorised access to commercially sensitive information australiaedit chc is the largest provider of emergency medical helicopter services in australiacitation needed militaryedit royal australian air force raaf  chc has been providing dedicated rescue support to the raaf since  where it operates sikorsky s policeedit victoria police air wing and air ambulance services  chc provides three eurocopter san dauphin and one eurocopter ec aircraft plus maintenance services to the victoria police ambulanceedit snowy hydro southcare multipurpose helicopter in australia fire and emergency services authority of western australia  based in perth wa chc provides a bell  ep aircraft ambulance victoria  up until the end of  chc provided two bell ep helicopters for air ambulance and search and rescue duties ambulance service of new south wales  chc provides three aws and two ec helicopters to supplement ambulance nsws eight contracted aeromedical helicopters these are based at wollongong sydney and orange new south wales snowy hydro southcare air ambulance service  chc operates a bell  for emergency helicopter service based in symonston australian capital territory norwayedit norwegian search and rescue  chc provides private search and rescue services in the norwegian sector of the north sea but acts in concert with the norwegian rescue coordination centres the chc sar fleet includes two super puma l and three super puma ec  other related servicesedit nh chc is designing manufacturing and installing  liferaft assembly kits for the nh helicopter a new military search and rescue helicopter provided to the military of several european countries through a joint venture shared by agusta eurocopter and fokker supply rescue and support services chc provides extensive ship supply and rescue service off the coast of africa and the netherlands and helicopter support services to scientific expeditions in antarctica and other harsh environments fleetedit chc operates approximately  aircraft in over  countries which include malaysia australia brazil thailand the philippines the middle east south africa ecuador angola gabon and equatorial guinea helicoptersedit   agustawestland aw   eurocopter super puma as l l   eurocopter ec   eurocopter as n n n dauphin   sikorsky s a and c series   sikorsky s   bell    airbus ec  locationsedit  australia new south wales sydney • orange • wollongong • newcastle victoria melbourne • latrobe valley • bendigo western australia perth • karratha • broome  bangladesh  brazil  canada british columbia richmond delta nova scotia halifax  denmark esbjerg  india  indonesia  ireland cork • dublin • shannon • waterford • sligo  malaysia  norway stavanger • bergen • florø • kristiansund • brønnøysund  netherlands den helder  philippines  scotland • aberdeen • sumburgh  thailand  united kingdom • norwich • humberside accidents and incidentsedit on march   chc sikorsky s operating as rescue  crashed into the sea off blacksod west of ireland  fatalities  missing on april   a chc ec crashed near turøy norway killing all  occupants on august   a chc super puma l crashed  nm from sumburgh in the shetlands scotland the aircraft crashed into the sea killing  passengers and the remaining  passengers and  crew were rescued see alsoedit  chc helicopters eurocopter as crash canadian helicopters chc airways referencesedit  chc group reports fourth quarter and full year  resultsaccessdate   company profile for chc helico